entries.femaleVariant: Time to see if this tastes as good as it smells.
[Sit] Seems change has done you some good.
River's discovering the joys of family life.
That and police duty – never a good mix. This here's a way to get some of those years back.
Unemployment's bein' good to you, ya seem good.
I haven't seen him this... untroubled in a while.
What about you, V? You got a family, or just relations?
Well... you brought my family back to me, and I'm grateful.
Grab a seat.
Used to think family was nothing but baggage.
Was a nomad, had that family, but it fell apart.
Heywood's my family.
Used to see family as baggage, something that'd hold me back. You know, career first.
Used to be a nomad, but the family fell apart.
Grew up in Heywood. Whole street was my family.
Not sure I'm cut out for it.
Don't have one, don't want one.
Like to have one someday.
Family's a breeding ground for pain. Not sure I'm cut out for it.
Can barely take care of myself as is.
Don't have one, don't want one.
No place for me in one, and I just don't need it.
If the future allows it, I... I'd like to have one someday.
If for no other reason than that I love get-togethers like this.
Didn't do any better for not havin' one, though.
Years ago, feels like.
Neighbors helped each other out, thought nothin' of it.
Nothin's more important to me than my kids.
See me as parent material?
Be great if Randy was here.
Joss, you see me bein' a parent, ever?
Speaking of, be great if Randy was here.
Won't be long.
Randy loooves jambalaya.
I mean, I don't exactly look like good mom material myself, so…
Yes, who says yes?
Phew, situation was gettin' dicey.
That's what partners are for.
Thanks, Joss!
If you say so, Joss...
And my brother likes you.
Joss...
Well, why hide it?
Out to set me up with River?
River prolly asked you to say that.
C'mon, Joss, you don't see wedding bells in my future, surely.
Why not?
Who thinks V and Uncle River make a good couple?
Prolly asked you to say that himself, didn't he?
Wow – how did she know?
Hey! Food's on the table!
I've made mistakes, life's gone off the rails sometimes, but I had my kids... I got my kids.
[Raise hand] Me!
Well, that's decided.
Got an 11-99, officer needs backup.
C'mon, pull you outta this ambush.
Yeah, thanks!
I do!
Here we are.
What're we lookin' at?
A water tower. Great spot.
Lemme give you a boost. Climb over, open it from the other side.
Yeah, OK, good.
[Jump the fence] OK.
Apparently the worst city between the Atlantic and the Pacific.
But I sure do love this view. Find it calming.
I see what you're doin', River.
And how am I doin'? Do I stand a chance?
I can't, River. I'm sorry.
River, I… I can't. I'm sorry.
You're turnin' down the best damn lover in this whole trailer park.
Friends?
Yeah... friends.
I can see what you're doin'.
I like you, but not like that.
Listen, River… if you expect this to evolve somehow…
Don't stand a chance, do I?
Maybe we keep it at friends.
Yeah. Sure.
[Drink] To friendship.
[Drink] To Joss and the kids.
[Drink] To Night City.
Here's to Joss and the kids.
Yeah, to family.
To friendship.
To friendship.
Just don't fall in love…
We're friends. Rather keep it that way.
Just don't fall in love with me…
Too late, V.
Up for a drink?
Got any more of that?
Two bottles of whiskey and a case of beer oughta be enough.
We'll see about that.
Buckle your liver in. Gonna be a long night and a longer morning, heh.
Christ, V. Can't believe you're makin' me fuck a cop.
Gonna go plug my ears, gouge out my eyes.
Yeah. I like where we are now, right here, outside lookin' in.
Away from all the urban chaos. Reminds me a bit of home.
entries.maleVariant: Away from all the urban chaos. It reminds me a bit of home.

entries.femaleVariant: I dunno, River...
'Scrapers kinda clutter it up for me.
View's to die for. Great spot, indeed.
Told ya…
[Sit] Love this spot, too.
[Sit] Skyscrapers are in the way.
[Sit] I like where we are right now.
[Sit] Those corps trash the streets from their temples.
[Sit] Can't see the shit in those 'scrapers from here.
Please don't string me along.
That a pick-up line?
Ever feel lonely?
That the pick-up line you settled on?
'Cause, maybe heard three in my life that were worse, and just a little at that.
entries.maleVariant: 'Cause, heard maybe three in my life that were worse, and just a little at that.

entries.femaleVariant: Wouldn't mind hearin' 'em.
Yeah? Happy to oblige.
Ever feel alone?
'Course I do. But doubt I'm cut out for relationships.
I doubt you know who you're talkin' to. Me, I'm a master of disastrous relationships.
I'll need some evidence.
Out here, you can't smell the shit the corps dump on the streets.
Like the city's their own personal toilet. Shit, flush, repeat.
Hm, poetic, couldn’t'a said it better.
'Scrapers actually seem pretty majestic from out here, not seein' what goes on inside.
entries.maleVariant: Scrapers actually seem pretty majestic out here, not seein' what goes on inside.

entries.femaleVariant: Memories?
High stress, dirty backstabs, kind of pressure that gives you ulcers…
Somehow I just don't miss it.
Now for the highlight of the evening.
Here's to that fuckin' city.
To Night City.
You're just gettin' out of doin' the dishes, admit it.
Also true. Which gives us two reasons to go.
This a romantic stroll, by chance?
Not about to pick you flowers, if that's what you're askin'.
This way-- Ah, fuck, gate's stuck again. Gonna fix it one of these days.
"You swallow beautifully."
"You got two wishes left."
"I'll fuck you for free."
"Way you swallow – beautiful."
Hah… You serious?
This guy and I, sitting at a diner.
entries.maleVariant: This guy and I, sittin' at a diner.

entries.femaleVariant: Five minutes he gapes at me, not a word, then drops that bomb.
Oof...
So I'm at a bar and this gonk taps me on the shoulder and says, "Here I am, baby. You got two wishes left."
What'd you say?
Spoke my second wish – that he would fuck off.
Was there a third?
Mhm. Wished him a speedy recovery. Broken arm – merciful, I'd say.
OK, last one was good.
Y'know, woman once told me I have sexy calves.
That's it?
Just like her boyfriend's... before he lost his legs in the war.
Yiiikes.
She was right, though. I do have great calves.
Was in love once.
Broke a boyfriend's jaw.
Sent a boyfriend skydiving once.
Was only ever in love once. I was a shithead, while he was... he was great.
Buuut...?
Well, he had...quirks, between the sheets, I mean. Found that out later.
Couldn't get hard without a mask on. And not the Venetian carnival kind, but US presidents. A closet full.
The hell…?
Had to dump him. Could only fuck Honest Abe so many times.
Hahaha... you made that up. C'mon, admit it.
Smashed one relationship to pieces along with the fucker's jaw.
Why, what'd he do?
Said I was too aggressive for him.
Kidding... He had a side bitch, caught 'em fucking between the sheets I'd bought.
entries.maleVariant: Kidding... He had a side piece, caught 'em fucking between the sheets I'd bought.

entries.femaleVariant: Oof... classic.
Booked a skydiving experience for this one guy I was dating...
And he never came back.
Ah, V, I'm sorry... I know what it means when somebody close dies.
Dies? No... no-no-no, just, fallin' outta that plane he fell in love with his instructor.
entries.maleVariant: Dies? No, no... just, in fallin' outta that plane he fell in love with his instructor.

entries.femaleVariant: Nice story, but it don't beat my last serious liaison.
What'd you do?
I shot her.
Shuddup…
Had no choice. Found ourselves standing on opposite sides of the law.
But don't worry, never made it a habit. I'm done shooting the women I date.
entries.maleVariant: But don't worry, never made it a habit. I'm done shooting the people I date.

entries.femaleVariant: Area's not bad, actually. Unlikely to dazzle, make a good first impression, though.
Certainly no Corpo Plaza.
No, but life's livable here. Know of worse places to raise kids.
Randy's problems with the law? Those didn't pop outta thin air…
True, but Randy takes after his old man. He'd find trouble in a nicer neighborhood, too.
Got something for you.
[Take] Your pistol?
[Take] What's the occasion?
Your piece?
Had her a long time. Too long. I think it's time she found a new owner.
Dunno what to say...
Wow. What's the occasion?
Aimin' to close a door, a stage of my life is done. This thing holds too many memories, won't let me do that. It'll serve you better.
Thank you.
Just promise you won't blow your foot off.
Oddly specific request.
Joss's husband did it. Drunk. This very spot.
Which made this your special spot! Family landmark?
Somethin' of the kind.
You were about a hair's breadth away from havin' to look at photo albums.
No need.
Just push. Seems easier to open from that side.
[Open] OK.
OK…!
All right, V. You know why we're here, don't ya? Say you do.
OK, that'd be about all the funny stories I got tonight.
Somethin' strong's sure to hit the spot.
Got some lemonade, anything in that vein?
Got some lemonade or somethin' in that vein?
Somethin' strong would sure hit the spot.
Sure you don't mind me drinkin'? Probably lots more?
[Raise hand] I do!
Hahah, I do!
Haha, she raised her hand herself! Hihi!
entries.maleVariant: Haha, he raised his hand himself! Hihi!

entries.femaleVariant: V, are you seeing someone, involved? Fess up, please!
Hahaha, V just voted!
Havin' a drink, shootin' the shit.
Great for what?
For, y'know... the views.
The views... Right.
No, no, seriously!
"I'll fuck you for free."
Hahaha... what...?!
Got a contract – to pull info out of a gigolo in a techmink fedora.
entries.maleVariant: I got a contract – to pull info out of a gigolo in a techmink fedora.

entries.femaleVariant: It was weird, he was spilliiin'… And then he pulled that one out of his hat.
entries.maleVariant: It was weird, he was spillin'… Then he pulled that one out of his hat.

entries.femaleVariant: A candid and generous proposal, V. You should've at least considered it.
All right. We can still have a drink.
Now that I understand.
Lemon--? Heh… well, sure, but seriously?
Was supposed to be a family dinner. Wasn't expecting... hard lubrication.
No, you kiddin'? Your spot, this, your customs.
You'll hang with me, though? I can be awfully charming when drunk.
Hm. We'll see.
Too late.
Umm...
Whoa, OK! We like leapin'!
On our way…
[Kiss] To us.
To us.
Whoooa... V... What're you doin'?
Sorry, I--I thought...
Right... Listen...
Look, no need to explain. I get it. And it's fine.
So, was your game fun?
Awesome! We kicked their big butts!
It was OK. V's pretty nova, I guess.
Huh? Oh, yeah the bad guys, too!
The bad guys?
Maybe you oughta play together more often, huh?
Mhm! But she's on my team next time!
entries.maleVariant: Mhm! But he's on my team next time!

entries.femaleVariant: [Kiss]
[Eat]
[Stand]
